The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Kapil heads awards panel

New Delhi: Indias lone world-Cup winning captain Kapil Dev will chair the 15-member committee for selecting this years Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna the countrys highest sporting honour Arjuna awardees and winner of the Dhyanchand award for lifetime achievement. 

The committee includes prominent sports personalities such as Olympic bronze medallist weightlifter Karnam Malleshwari, athlete P.T. Usha and shooter Anjali Bhagwat. 

Iconic shuttler Prakash Padukone will head another 15-member committee, constituted to choose the winner of Dronacharya award for coaches. 

Former tennis player Nirupama Mankad, ace shooter Soma Shirur and Michael Ferreira are among the committee members. 

